<taxonomicName family="Oryidae" genus="S." kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="S. bahiensis" order="Scolopendromorpha" pageId="5" pageNumber="18" rank="species" species="bahiensis">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="18">S. bahiensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is usually found in the semi-arid regions of Bahia and Minas Gerais. This study recorded its occurrence for the first time in a quartzitic cave from Minas Gerais. Accidental in caves.
</paragraph>
